Group A: Short Questions (2 Marks)
1. Define Information Architecture (IA).
Information Architecture (IA) is the process of organizing, structuring, and labeling 
website content so that users can easily find and understand information.
It focuses on navigation, menus, categories, and content hierarchy.

2. What is a “Wireframe”?
A wireframe is a basic visual blueprint of a website that shows the layout and placement 
of elements like headers, menus, content areas, and buttons without colors or images.
It helps designers plan structure before actual development.

3. Explain the concept of “Cognitive Friction” in web design.
Cognitive friction refers to the mental effort required by users when a website is 
confusing, cluttered, or difficult to navigate.
High cognitive friction makes users feel frustrated and increases bounce rate.

4. Why should URL slugs use hyphens instead of underscores?
Hyphens (-) are preferred because search engines treat hyphens as word separators, while underscores (_) are not.
Example:
web-design-basics (Good for SEO)
web_design_basics (Poor readability & SEO)

